    public class InventoryManager : MonoBehaviour {
        int slotID = -1; //id of the previously clicked slot

        public void OnPointerClick(PointerEventData eventData) {
            if (this.slotID != selectedItem.id) {
                this.slotID = selectedItem.id;
                //your code for a single click
            } else {
                this.slotID = -1; //clear the slot id;
                //your code for a double click
            }
        }
    }
Now there still remains the timing problem: This way it will always trigger the single click event and then the double click event. If you want to conditionally skip the single click event, you could make it wait for a second before triggerign the single click event. Hopefully the single click event does not much, so you can adjust the double click handler to undo what the single click handler did.  
E.g. if an item was picked up and the user immediately clicks the same slot a second time, you can just place the item back in the slot and execute the event for a double click. A timer is probably optional as long as it&#39;s possible to undo the single click.

